1 957

A year ago today I was working on the index.

Spent part of the day putting away the material that had been used in the Public Library exhibit and was returned yesterday.

Watched a couple of football games on TV.

Carded some recent acquisitions, particularly the Venom Symposium.

1 957

At the office this morning. Got an emergency call to the federal court where they were selecting a jury for the Convair-Carlstrom case. At the court from 2 PM to 4. Was drawn as an alternate juror and then excused because of my relationship with Jay Gould, as Lyon Van and Storage is one of the defendants.

Then paid bills and wrote letters. Also began to round up income tax data.

1 957

Went to the St. Francis and registered but no room. Then to Berkeley arriving at the U C Press at 9:45. Talked to Liienthal, Miss Bunting, Quail Hawkins, Callenbach, and Mrs. Carroll and got the latest information about sales, promotion, etc. Left data with Mrs. Carroll for exhibit at the U.C.Library. Took her to a sandwich joint for lunch and caught the 12:48 for S.F..

Acted as chairman of the meeting (the first) of the State Chamber of Commerce Committee on Atomic Energy. This was from 2 to 4; it was a good organization meeting.

Back to the hotel and got a room.

Took Tova and Bob to dinner at the Prime Rib 7-9:15.

Page Edit History:
  • pamg 09/23/2012 08:34 PM
  • BPOC 05/10/2012 01:01 PM

1 957

Attended a meeting of the directors of the State Chamber of Commerce with luncheon from 10 to 1. Then checked out and got rid of my baggage at the S. P. Depot. Made the mistake of checking my coat and got caught in the rain later.

Then went out the the U. C. Medical Center (Moffelt Hospital) to see the exhibit of my book they had put together. This was arranged in 5 or 6 wall cases; they had done a lot of work on it and it was quite good, even to a fake piece of manuscript they had written by hand. Had photos taken.

Called on Dorrie with Mrs. Carroll. We visited her from about 3 to 5. Then picked up Chris Carroll at his school and they dropped me at Blums.

Caught the lark

1957

Went to a meeting of the Light and Power Council in the P.G. and E. directors room at 10. Met a lot of the old guard, whom I hadn't seen for several years. Bohemian Club for lunch.

Then to a meeting of the Atomic Committee of the state Chamber of Commerce where I presided. This lasted from 2 to 4. There was an interesting discussion of the many problems involved, especially in power generation.

Called Chickering's office but neither Allen, Sr. nor Sherwin were there.

Went out to A.J.'s and Dory's to take them to dinner. Had difficulty finding a place; one Rancho closed for the week; the other too crowded. Finally dined a the Town House in the Lakeside district. Then back to Dory's for a short time.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(May 27 Continued)

Reworked the material for tonight's talk at Stanford, and got it in fairly good shape.

Packing the car at Berkeley and unpacking at Redwood was quite tiring.

Went to the Stanford Natural History Museum at 5:40, then on to the Vieux Carre for dinner, sort of in our honor. There were 13 present. There were 5 vacant seats which I later found out were for GG's cousins whom we had not expected or advised.

Then to the Women's Lounge in the Union but this proved too small so we moved on to Jordan Hall. There were about 70 present. Talked on the Folklore of Rattlers from about 8:30 to 9:45. The interest seemed good. Some questions were asked.

Page Edit History:
  • lwilliams 07/11/2014 03:45 PM
  • pamg 09/29/2012 01:16 PM
  • BPOC 05/10/2012 01:01 PM

1 957

Went to the main U.C. Library at 8:40 and saw the exhibit of 50 best books published in 1956. Artistic and novelty jobs, mostly. There was only one U.C. Press publication - on John Marin's paintings.

Saw Stebbins at MVZ and we had quite a chat. He told me of his research work on the pineal eye. Saw his experimental animals, including skellies and 2 sphenodono. Also saw Loye and Alden Miller.

Next to the U.C. Press where I saw Callenbach, Quail Hawkins, Rita Carroll, Philip Lilienttral, John Goetz, Fruge, Virginia Bunting. Talked with Callenbach about present and future reviews and publicity and with Silienthal about the Argosy article. Sales to date 1161 copies.

Left Berkeley at 11:20 and got to Redwood City at 11:40 where we put up at the El Camino Motel, where we had stopped on previous trips.

(Continued on May 26)

So our trip to Chicago and Des Moines is off, as well as the LA operas for which we have tickets for 7, talks at USC and UCLA and many other activities. Have to go to the hospital for 5 days or so for medication.

Started taking Paratrate.
